race.comment: BOULDER JACK (8) was brave at Bendigo when only nailed late after doing plenty of work on speed. Has the gate speed to offset the draw and looks set to give another bold sight. JENNI LA ROCK (9) showed pace at Ballarat before fading late. Will press forward again and is capable of sticking on strongly. COSMIC CHARGER (2) broke through at Avoca with a tough win and while drawn wide, he's worth including. THE BANTAM (3) has yet to break through this campaign but hasn't been far away including a last start third over 1550m at Manangatang. Looking for another fair run. BON'S BLING (17) form has dropped off in last two after a win at Ballarat Synthetic three runs back. Can bounce.
